law.text:
The following agricultural products and commodities are not subject to valuation or to property tax:
crops or the produce of any land in the possession of the producer or the agent of the producer;
fish in the possession of persons catching, salting, or packing the fish or in the possession of agents until sold;
poultry, including hatchery eggs;
tobacco stored in the State tobacco warehouse; and
regardless of whether they are in their original package, green coffee beans:
imported from a foreign country;
that are owned by and in possession of the importer; and
in which no physical or chemical change has been made by any manufacturing process.
